33 SECTION 8. G.S. 160D-403, as amended by S.L. 2024-49, reads as rewritten:
34 "§ 160D-403. Administrative development approvals and determinations.
35 (a) Development Approvals. – To the extent consistent with the scope of regulatory
36 development regulation authority granted by this Chapter, no person shall commence or proceed
37 with development without first securing any required development approval from the local
38 government with jurisdiction over the site of the development. A development approval shall be
39 in writing and may contain a provision requiring the development to comply with all applicable
40 State and local laws. A local government may issue development approvals in print or electronic
41 form. Any development approval issued exclusively in electronic form shall be protected from
42 further editing once issued. Applications for development approvals may be made by the
43 landowner, a lessee or person holding an option or contract to purchase or lease land, or an
44 authorized agent of the landowner. An easement holder may also apply for development approval
45 for such the development as is authorized by the easement.
46 (a1) Time Period for Approval. – Within 14 calendar days of the filing of an application
47 for a development approval, a local government or its designated administrative staff, as
48 described under G.S. 160D-402, shall (i) determine whether the application is complete and
49 notify the applicant of the application's completeness and, (ii) if the local government or its
50 designated administrative staff determines the application is incomplete, specify all of the
51 deficiencies in the notice to the applicant. The applicant may file an amended application or
