34 "§ 160D-944. Designation of historic districts.
35 (a) Any local government may, as part of a zoning regulation adopted pursuant to Article
36 7 of this Chapter or as a development regulation enacted or amended pursuant to Article 6 of this
37 Chapter, designate and from time to time amend one or more historic districts within the area
38 subject to the development regulation. Historic districts established pursuant to this Part shall
39 consist of areas that are deemed to be of special significance in terms of their history, prehistory,
40 architecture, or culture and to possess integrity of design, setting, materials, feeling, and
41 association.
42 A development regulation may treat historic districts either as a separate use district
43 classification or as districts that overlay other zoning districts. Where historic districts are
44 designated as separate use districts, the zoning development regulation may include as uses by
45 right or as special uses those uses found by the preservation commission to have existed during
46 the period sought to be restored or preserved or to be compatible with the restoration or
47 preservation of the district.
48 (b) No historic district or districts shall be designated under subsection (a) of this section
49 until all of the following occur:
