1 "§ 160D-1403.1. Civil action for declaratory relief, injunctive relief, other remedies; joinder
2 of complaint and petition for writ of certiorari in certain cases.
3 (a) Civil Action. – Except as otherwise provided in this section for claims involving
4 questions of interpretation, in lieu of any remedies available under G.S. 160D-405 or
5 G.S. 160D-108(h), a person with standing, as defined in subsection (b) of this section, may bring
6 an original civil action seeking declaratory relief, injunctive relief, damages, or any other
7 remedies provided by law or equity, in superior court or federal court to challenge the
8 enforceability, validity, or effect of a local land development regulation or development approval
9 for any of the following claims:
10 (1) The ordinance, development regulation, either on its face or as applied, is
11 unconstitutional.
12 (2) The ordinance, development regulation, either on its face or as applied, is ultra
13 vires, preempted, arbitrary or capricious, or is otherwise in excess of statutory
14 authority.
15 (3) The ordinance, development regulation, either on its face or as applied,
16 constitutes a taking of property.
17 (4) The development approval is ultra vires, preempted, in excess of its statutory
18 authority, made upon unlawful procedure, made in error of law, arbitrary and
19 capricious, or an abuse of discretion.
20 (a1) Appeals of Administrative Decisions. – If the decision development approval being
