1 (b) In any action in which a city or county is a party, upon finding by the court that the
2 city or county took action inconsistent with, or in violation of, G.S. 160D-108(b) or
3 G.S. 143-755, the court shall award reasonable attorneys' fees and costs to the party who
4 successfully challenged the local government's failure to comply with any of those provisions.
5 (c) In all other matters, matters not covered by subsection (a) or (b) of this section, the
6 court may award reasonable attorneys' fees and costs to the prevailing private litigant.
7 (d) For purposes of this section, "unambiguous" means that the limits of authority are not
8 reasonably susceptible to multiple constructions."
9 SECTION 27. Article 11 of Chapter 130A of the General Statutes is amended by
10 adding a new section to read:
11 "§ 130A-343.5. Wastewater systems for property within service area of a public or
12 community wastewater system.
13 (a) Notwithstanding G.S. 130A-55(16), 153A-284, 160A-317, 162A-6(a)(14d), and
14 162A-14(2), a property owner may install a wastewater system in accordance with this Article to
15 serve any undeveloped or unimproved property located so as to be served by a public or
16 community wastewater system.
17 (b) Notwithstanding G.S. 130A-55(16), 153A-284, 160A-317, 162A-6(a)(14d), and
18 162A-14(2), a property owner of developed or improved property located so as to be served by
19 a public or community wastewater system may install a wastewater system in accordance with
20 this Article if the public or community wastewater system has not yet installed sewer lines
21 directly available to the property or otherwise cannot provide wastewater service to the property
22 at the time the property owner desires wastewater service.
23 (c) Upon compliance with this Article, the property owner installing a wastewater system
24 pursuant to subsection (a) or (b) of this section shall not be required to connect to the public or
25 community wastewater system for so long as the wastewater system installed in accordance with
26 this Article remains compliant and in use. A property owner may opt to connect to the public or
27 community wastewater system if the property owner so desires.
28 (d) Nothing in this section shall require a property owner to install a wastewater system
29 in accordance with this Article if the property is located so as to be served by a public or
30 community wastewater system and the public or community wastewater system is willing to
31 provide wastewater service to the property.
32 (e) This section shall not apply, and a public or community wastewater system may
33 mandate connection to that public or community wastewater system, in any of the following
34 situations:
35 (1) The wastewater system in accordance with this Article serving the property
36 has failed and cannot be repaired.
37 (2) The public authority or unit of government operating the public water system
38 is being assisted by the Local Government Commission.
39 (3) The public authority or unit of government operating the public or community
40 wastewater system is in the process of expanding or repairing the public or
41 community wastewater system and is actively making progress to having
42 wastewater lines installed and directly available to provide wastewater service
43 to that property within the 24 months of the time the property owner applies
44 for a permit under this Article."
